parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents, loss of control, and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle hesitates or lags when shifting
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the check transmission light illuminates
the "E" indicator appears on the gear selector
the vehicle shakes or vibrates excessively
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wheel Bearing and Differential Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing and differential seal can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents, loss of control, and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Odor of gear oil leaking from the differential
particularly after highway driving
and repeated failure of the left rear wheel bearing and left differential seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, reduced performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine overheats at idle or while driving
especially in heavy traffic conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension and steering components can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle drifts or pulls to one side
loud slamming sounds from the front passenger and driver side
and the wheel turns excessively when encountering small bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking power, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the traction control light flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, accidents, and strandings.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical components and water leaks can cause electrical failures, corrosion, and accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into the electrical components
the sunroof drain hoses fail
and electrical components malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause engine misfires, reduced performance, and increased emissions.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the engine runs rough
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and handling issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates excessively at highway speeds
the vehicle drifts or pulls to one side
and the wheel turns excessively when encountering small bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the sudden and unexpected distraction, loss of control, and obstruction of the driver's vision.
symptoms: The airbag deploys suddenly and without warning
often accompanied by a loud noise
smoke
or powder
and can cause injuries to the driver and passengers
including bruises
burns
and hearing damage.
